<subSubSection lastPageId="6" lastPageNumber="626" pageId="5" pageNumber="625" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="5.[160,1155,1633,1727]" box="[160,286,1633,1658]" pageId="5" pageNumber="625">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[160,286,1633,1658]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="625">Comments</emphasis>
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="5.[160,1155,1633,1727]" pageId="5" pageNumber="625">
This species differs from 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Antennal" baseAuthorityName="Breuning" baseAuthorityYear="1940" box="[455,579,1668,1693]" class="Insecta" family="Cerambycidae" genus="Pseudoperma" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="5" pageNumber="625" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="patruelis">
<emphasis box="[455,579,1668,1693]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="625">P. patruelis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
in the rounded antennal tubercles and the lessevident median longitudinal vittae of the pronotum. It differs from 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Zajciw" authorityYear="1972" box="[914,1083,1702,1727]" class="Insecta" family="Cerambycidae" genus="Pseudoperma" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="5" pageNumber="625" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="chalcograma">
<emphasis box="[914,1083,1702,1727]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="625">P. chalcograma</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
in the
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="6.[160,1155,142,201]" pageId="6" pageNumber="626">coalescent or uninterrupted vittae of the elytra, and in having the mesosternal process anteriorly declivous, subtuberculate.</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
